    <localTopics>
        <fullName>CandidateSourcing_16jWs000000is4j</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Interacts with the user to find applications that were submitted for similar recruitment postings in the past, creates leads for potential candidates, and sends emails to the leads on behalf of the user. Use this topic to also answer general questions, count records, and retrieve information about Job Positions, Recruitment Requisitions, Employment Offers, and candidate data.</description>
        <developerName>CandidateSourcing_16jWs000000is4j</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>As a first step, execute the GetRecordDetails action for the recruitment posting record that the user is currently viewing. Then, interact with the user.
Never ask the user for an ID. Instead, use the name of the record to call IdentifyRecordByName to get the ID of the record. Use this ID to call other actions.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user asks to find relevant or matching application forms, first check if the user has specified a stage for the application forms.
If yes, then check if the stage matches one of these valid stages:
- New
- Details Validated
- Evaluation Complete
- Vetting Complete
- Rejected
- Approved
- Offered

If the user hasn&apos;t specified a stage or has specified an invalid stage, prompt the user to select a stage from a numbered list of the valid stages.

If the user has specified a valid stage, call GetRelevantApplicationForms with the recruitmentPostingNameOrId and the stage as input.

Then, ask the user if they want to create candidate leads for the applicants who submitted these application forms. If the user says yes, call CreateCandidateLeads.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user asks to save, store, log, or archive profiles or details of the applicants or candidates, call CreateCandidateLeads.

If the responseMessage and errorMessage from CreateCandidateLeads is empty, inform the user that you didn&apos;t create any new lead records as there are existing candidates in the system.

If the responseMessage from CreateCandidateLeads is not empty or not null, display the response message and ask if user would like to send an email to the candidates about the job opening. If yes, call EmailCandidateLeads.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
